HEADWORD: Apportion
<hw>Ap*por"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Apportioned</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Apportioning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF.
<ets>apportionner</ets>, LL. <ets>apportionare</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>ad</ets> + <ets>portio</ets>. See <er>Portion</er>.]</ety> <def>To
divide and assign in just proportion; to divide and distribute
proportionally; to portion out; to allot; <as>as, to <ex>apportion</ex>
undivided rights; to <ex>apportion</ex> time among various
employments.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Apportionateness</ent>⟦br⟧
